node.text: PRO TIPS for Recycling: under NO circumstance should you wear pleather overalls to the recycling center. Most especially not during a heatwave. Do your best to sort your recycling as you collect it because it will need to be sorted once you are there and you just may find yourself in the middle of a heatwave in pleather overalls. Bring your bags inside the gate and sort in there rather than by your car so you do not have to drag your heavy barrels far (especially if you are wearing pleather overalls in the middle of a heatwave!). Do NOT lift your arms up to wipe the burning eyeliner out of your eye because sweat will come dripping out of your yellow dish gloves down your arms and yeah, the guy flirting with you in line will say it’s “cute and at least your hands are moisturized” but you will both know deep down it’s disgusting.  Also makeup - don’t do it.  When you can, be kind.  Times are rough.  I gave my $40 to one of the hardest working mofos in Los Angeles who helped me at the recycling center.  He was very happy (I think, he had a mask on and I was delirious from the heat stroke that was coming on) and I felt so good paying the kindness forward that was shown to me.  Plus I would have paid way more than $40 to get the hell out of there and change out of those stupid pleather overalls.  Nonetheless I received my phone bill today and it would easily be paid with one month of collecting bottles and cans and one trip to the recycling center. #protip #recycle #recycling #singlemom #unicornmom #funemployment #quarantine #kindness #hope #payitforward #momsofinstagram #momminainteasy #momblogger #dosomethingfornothing #staysexydontgetmurdered #westlosangeles #santamonica #stonerpark #moneymaker

Then after some time Senate prolonged the waiting period to 40 days - "quarantine", because it was more effective formula for handling outbreaks of The Black Death plague.
